<longTitle>
<docTitle class="centered fontsize12" style="-uslm-lc:I658005">An Act</docTitle>
<officialTitle class="indentUp0 firstIndent1 fontsize8" style="-uslm-lc:I658011">To require the Federal Communications Commission to issue an order providing that a shark attack is an event for which a wireless emergency alert may be transmitted, and for other purposes.<sidenote><p class="centered fontsize8" id="x7dcc45a6-85e5-11f1-9a3e-790350fb9735" style="-uslm-lc:I658076"><approvedDate date="2026-06-26">June 26, 2026</approvedDate></p><p class="centered fontsize8" id="x7dcc45a7-85e5-11f1-9a3e-790350fb9735" style="-uslm-lc:I658076">[<ref href="/us/bill/119/s/1003">S. 1003</ref>]<?GPOvSpace 08?></p></sidenote></officialTitle>
</longTitle>
<enactingFormula style="-uslm-lc:I658120"><i>  Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representa­tives of the United States of America in Congress assembled,</i></enactingFormula><sidenote><p class="leftAlign firstIndent0 fontsize8" id="x7dcc93c8-85e5-11f1-9a3e-790350fb9735" style="-uslm-lc:I658180">Lulu’s Law.</p><p class="leftAlign firstIndent0 fontsize8" id="x7dcc93c9-85e5-11f1-9a3e-790350fb9735" style="-uslm-lc:I658180"><ref href="/us/usc/t47/s1201">47 USC 1201 note</ref>.</p></sidenote>
<section id="d155e92" identifier="/us/pl/119/100/s1" style="-uslm-lc:I658146"><num class="bold" value="1">SECTION 1. </num><heading>SHORT TITLE.</heading><content style="-uslm-lc:I658120">  This Act may be cited as “<shortTitle role="act">Lulu’s Law</shortTitle>”.</content></section>
<section id="d155e102" identifier="/us/pl/119/100/s2" style="-uslm-lc:I658141"><num class="fontsize12" value="2">SEC. 2. </num><heading class="fontsize12">WIRELESS EMERGENCY ALERTS.</heading><subsection class="firstIndent0 fontsize10" id="y7dcf79fa-85e5-11f1-9a3e-790350fb9735" identifier="/us/pl/119/100/s2/a" role="definitions" style="-uslm-lc:I658120"><num class="fontsize10" style="-uslm-lc:emspace2" value="a">(a) </num><heading class="fontsize10"><inline class="smallCaps">Definition</inline>.—</heading><content>In this section, the term “<term>Alert Message</term>” has the meaning given the term in <ref href="/us/cfr/t47/s10.10/a">section 10.10(a) of title 47, Code of Federal Regulations</ref>, or any successor regulation.</content></subsection>
<subsection class="firstIndent0 fontsize10" id="y7dcfa10b-85e5-11f1-9a3e-790350fb9735" identifier="/us/pl/119/100/s2/b" style="-uslm-lc:I658120"><num class="fontsize10" style="-uslm-lc:emspace2" value="b">(b) </num><sidenote><p class="leftAlign firstIndent0 fontsize8" id="x7dcfa10c-85e5-11f1-9a3e-790350fb9735" style="-uslm-lc:I658180">Deadline.</p></sidenote><heading class="fontsize10"><inline class="smallCaps">Requirement</inline>.—</heading><content>Not later than 180 days after the date of enactment of this Act, the Federal Communications Commission shall issue an order to provide that a shark attack is an event for which an Alert Message may be transmitted.</content></subsection>
</section>
<action>
<actionDescription style="-uslm-lc:I658030">Approved</actionDescription> <date date="2026-06-26">June 26, 2026</date>.</action>
